Deep Learning Overview
- Linear Classifier: basics of image classification using 
Support Vector Machines (SVM), loss functions, optimization, and backpropagation
- Artificial Neural Network (ANN) Foundations: individual neurons, activation functions (Sigmoid, ReLU, etc.), 
multi-layer fully connected network structures
- Training Deep Neural Networks: data preprocessing, gradient descent, learning rate selection, regularization techniques
- Transformer: Seg2seq architecture (self-attention, multi-head attention, positional encoding, applications)

RNN & Variants
- Basic RNN: Vanila RNN structures, weight sharing in time dimension, Back-Propagation Through Time
- RNN Training Issues: gradient vanishing, gradient clipping
- LSTM: gate structure, memory cells for long-term dependencies
- GRU: simplified LSTM variant which merges states and gates
- RNN applications: speech recognition, image captioning, text sentiment classification, text generation

RNN Extensions & DNC
- NTM: combining neural networks with external memory components
- DNC: neural networks with dynamic external memory
- theoretical foundations: approximation capabilities of RNNs and their Turing-complete nature

Computer Vision
- Visual Tasks: image classification, localization, object detection, semantic segmentation
- Object Detection Methods: R-CNN series, YOLO (You Only Look Once), SSD (Single Shot MultiBox Detector), and DETR (Detection Transformer)
- Image Segmentation: Full Convolutional Networks (FCN) and subsequent developments (SegNet, UNet, PSPNet, and Mask R-CNN)
- Transformer-based Segmentation: TransUnet and Swin Transformer for specialized tasks like medical image segmentation

Computer Vision & Autonomous Driving
- Self-Driving Principles: Differentiates between autonomous operation and Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS)
- Sensor Types and Data: role of Lidar, cameras, sonar, and GPS/GNSS in collecting the massive amounts of data required for perception
- Driving Perception: traffic sign detection, pedestrian and vehicle detection, path perception using networks like LaneNet and PilotNet

Multimodal Vision Large Models
- ViT: architecture for treating image patches as "words" for parallel training in a Transformer structure
- CLIP: aligns text and images in a common latent space via self-supervised learning
- MAE: asymmetric encoder-decoder architecture that learns by reconstructing missing pixels from highly masked image patches

LLM API Integration
- API usage: steps for applying for API keys, setting base URLs, and calling specific models through interfaces
- Dialogue Roles: System (instructions), User (requests), and Assistant (responses)
- Context Engineering: Addresses challenges like catastrophic forgetting and techniques for managing long-term memory and context compression

Mamba: Selective State Space Models
- State Space Models (SSM): continuous and discrete signal mapping using linear time-invariant systems
- Discretization: transforming continuous parameters into discrete ones using rules like Zero-Order Hold (ZOH)
- Mamba Architecture: selection mechanism and hardware-aware implementation (selective scan and kernel fusion) to achieve linear-time sequence modeling

Torchvision Object Detection
- Library Core: PyTorch-based library for CV tasks, containing pre-trained models and core modules for datasets, transforms, and operators
- OD Implementation: fine-tuning Faster R-CNN or SSD models, dataset definition, model modification, and training/testing workflows













